The paper discusses parallel adaptive mesh refinement and coarsening using a forest-of-octrees approach, which is a common topic in the field of distributed computing (cs.DC). The use of octrees also suggests a connection to numerical analysis (cs.NA) and data structures (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper discusses algorithms for operating on distributed forests of octrees, which could fall under the category of computational geometry (cs.CG) or mathematical software (cs.MS).
